== Description ==

The [[Image:Assembly_ConstraintDiameter.svg|16px]] [[Assembly3_ConstraintDiameter|Diameter]] command constrains the diameter of a 2D circle or arc which is made with [[Image:Workbench_Draft.svg|16px]] [[Draft_Workbench|Draft Workbench]] tools in relation with a [[Image:Assembly_Workplane.svg|16px]] workplane.

To set the diameter edit the Diameter parameter in the properties panel. 

== Usage ==

# Select a 2D '''circle''' or '''arc'''
# Activate the [[Image:Assembly_ConstraintDiameter.svg|16px]] [[Assembly3_ConstraintDiameter|Diameter]] command using the:
#* {{Button|[[Image:Assembly_ConstraintDiameter.svg|16px]] [[Assembly3_ConstraintDiameter|Diameter]]}} button.
# Set the '''Diameter''' value in the (constraint's) properties panel.
# Press the {{Button|[[Image:Assembly3_workbench_icon.svg|16px]] [[Assembly3_ResolveConstraints|Solve constraints]]}} or the {{Button|[[Image:Assembly_QuickSolve.svg|16px]] [[Assembly3_QuickSolve|Quick solve]]}} button to recompute 
:: (if {{Button|[[Image:Assembly_AutoRecompute.svg|16px]] [[Assembly3_AutoRecompute|Auto recompute]]}} and {{Button|[[Image:Assembly_SmartRecompute.svg|16px]] [[Assembly3_SmartRecompute|Smart recompute]]}} are disabled).


